{
  "_comment_tokens": "CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS is intentionally NOT set. The harness then uses the model's full per-response budget (Opus/Sonnet ≥ 32K, Haiku ≥ 8K). A static cap can truncate long edits/reviews mid-stream; the agent already runs across as many responses as the task needs, so a per-response cap is the wrong knob. Only set it if you actively want shorter replies (e.g. cost ceiling on a noisy skill).",
  "_comment_git": "git commit and git push BOTH require explicit confirmation. They are NOT in the allow list — every invocation prompts the user.",
  "_comment_automode": "defaultMode: auto enables autonomous execution for Sonnet AND Opus (Claude Code v2.1.83+). Requires Team/Enterprise/API plan — remove this key if you are on a Pro plan or want per-action prompts. Toggle mid-session with Shift+Tab.",
  "defaultMode": "auto",

